{"lemma":"حِينِ","slug":"حِينِ","root":"ح.#.ن","root_slug":"ح-_-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-_-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حِين","root":"حين","pos":"N","occurrence_count":35},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["conj","noun","prep","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n9800","n9801"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%86%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"time, moment"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"opportunity"},{"pos":"conj","gloss":"when"},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"at the time of, upon"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to update on"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَانَ (ḥāna) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Morphologically from the root ح ي ن (ḥ y n).\n\n*IPA⁽ᵏᵉʸ⁾: /ħaj.ja.na/"},"ipa":["/ħiːn/","/ħiː.na/","/ħajn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n9800","headword_ar":"حَيْنٌ","root":"Hyn","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Death; a state of destruction"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perdition:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time of the appointed term"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of life"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time of death."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 322.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A trial,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trying affliction."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n9801","headword_ar":"حِينٌ","root":"Hyn","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dahorN","text_ar":"دَهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a space,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"period, of time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (K:) or, accord. to EshSháfi'ee,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time, from the beginning of the world to its end;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dahorN","text_ar":"دَهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Az voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dahorN","text_ar":"دَهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, S, Mgh, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a vague sense,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, K,) applicable to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"little or much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long or short, that may be a year"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or [in some cases] particularly meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forty years:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seven years:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two years:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"six months:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two months:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any morning and evening:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a space of time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) as in the Kur lxxvi. I, (S,) and in the Kur xxxvii. 178: (K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a continuous time:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 381:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"day of resurrection;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coming to pass of the resurrection;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the Kur xxxviii. last verse: (Mgh, TA:) or it has two meanings; namely,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a time of unknown limit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also, as in the Kur xiv. 30,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"six months:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, Msb:) accord. to Er-Rághib, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time of"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arriving,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coming,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"happening;"},{"kind":"text","text":"having a vague meaning, and rendered particular, or special, by that to which it is prefixed: some say that it occurs applied in different ways: to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an appointed term;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as that to which God makes one to live: and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a year;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the Kur xiv. 30: and to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time"},{"kind":"text","text":"when an event takes place; as in the Kur xxx. 16: and to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time absolutely:"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to El-Munáwee, in the [genuine] language of the Arabs, it is applied to [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a glance of the eye,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more than that,"},{"kind":"text","text":"to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time without end:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHoyaAnN","text_ar":"اَحْيَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) and pl. pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHaAyiynu","text_ar":"اَحَايِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, * K;) as in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN yafoEalu ka*aA A^aHoyaAnFA","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ يَفْعَلُ كَذَا اَحْيَانًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY AlA^aHaAyiyni","text_ar":"فِى الاَحَايِينِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one does so at times,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sometimes"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) In the Kur [xiv. 30],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuw^otiY","text_ar":"تُوْتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ukulahaA kul~a HiynK","text_ar":"اُكُلَهَا كُلَّ حِينٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Which yieldeth its fruit"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"every six months:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, Msb, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"every year:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"every morning and evening:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to Az,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in every season, uninterruptedly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aYo'K","text_ar":"شَىْءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miHoyaAnu","text_ar":"مِحْيَانُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", also, means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hiynuhu","text_ar":"حِينُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"season, of a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) [You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY HiynK","text_ar":"اـِلَى حِينٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"For a time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"season."},{"kind":"text","text":"] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiynFA","text_ar":"حِينًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"At one time; sometime; at some time; awhile."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hiyna","text_ar":"حِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qumotu Hiyna qumota","text_ar":"قُمْتُ حِينَ قُمْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I stood in the time when thou stoodest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I stood when thou stoodest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is an adv. n. of time; (Msb;) [see also an ex. in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xa$afa","text_ar":"خَشَفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the remarks there subjoined:] and one may well employ in its place"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lam~aA","text_ar":"لَمَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*aA","text_ar":"اـِذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*o","text_ar":"اـِذْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mataY","text_ar":"مَتَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAEapa","text_ar":"سَاعَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqota","text_ar":"وَقْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA) and the like; but not, as many have said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hayovu","text_ar":"حَيْثُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for this is an adv. n. of place. (Msb.) ―         -b2-  When they make the two times to be distant, the one from the other, [i. e. the time of speaking and the time spoken of,] they do so by means of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_*","text_ar":"اـذ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and thus, (K,) they say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hiynay^i*K","text_ar":"حِينَيِذٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"At that time; then"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, K:) and sometimes they suppress the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", substituting for it"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b3-  Sometimes, also, they prefix"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ta","text_ar":"تَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hiyna","text_ar":"حِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, TA;) and say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA taHiyna","text_ar":"لَا تَحِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It is not,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was not, a time"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of such a thing; but this is generally written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laAta Hiyna","text_ar":"لَاتَ حِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as in the Kur xxxviii. 2 [respecting which see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lyt","text_ar":"ليت"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) Aboo-Wejzeh Es-Saadee says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"AaloEaATifuwna taHiyna maA mino EaATifK\n                      \n                     \n                        waAlmuToEimuwna zamaAna A^ayona AlmuToEiwu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The persons who return to the attack when there is none"},{"kind":"text","text":"other"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that returns to the attack,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(as is said in the S and L in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ETf","text_ar":"عطف"},{"kind":"text","text":",) or it may mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who act affectionately in the time when there is none"},{"kind":"text","text":"other"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that acts affectionately;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as is said in the L in that art.;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the feeders in the time when"},{"kind":"text","text":"it is said,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Where is the feeder?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) ISd says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"is thus prefixed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hyn","text_ar":"حين"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as it is in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"talaAna","text_ar":"تَلَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA=na","text_ar":"الا=نَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but IB says that Ibn-Es-Seeráfee cites the former hemistich thus:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"AaloEaATifuwnaho Hiyna maAmino EaATifK"},{"kind":"text","text":"[with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":"of pausation]: and some say that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":"of pausation is likened to the fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", and is then made movent with fet-h. (TA. [See more in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lyt","text_ar":"ليت"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b4-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiynapN","text_ar":"حِينَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":["K","Az","S","Mgh","Msb","TA","Fr"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}